I think it’s gonna be impossible to not compare this to Sideways. Both Alexander Payne movies starring Paul Giamatti as a failed intellectual who in their sadness have turned to alcohol. However, I left this movie thinking that this may be the better of the two. I think generally coming of age serves as a better backdrop for getting deeper themes across so it’s a little unfair to compare them. It provides an easy contrast between young and old, someone…
